Welcome 2023! #2023.  WOW what a story on this New year’s Eve! 
The last time going to see fireworks was 2019 in London when out of nowhere the fireworks broke down and there were none, there was a gut feeling that was not a good sign. 
Sure enough, 2020 happened.
The last time we had seen fireworks was 2018 in Dubai. 
Fast forward to this year, Hail was falling hurricane like winds, yeah in Cali, and no matter how much I prayed for fireworks it was a guaranteed NO by everyone I asked.
But I stayed the course, even with gusts of winds knocking over otherwise floating umbrellas.
I mean seriously, we had picked the best seats in the house. Sorry no fireworks tonight (oh my another 2020?)
Then God did a little showing off 😉 
AS ONLY HE CAN, so I winked at him at midnight, hearing his message LOUD and CLEAR!
Happy New Year Everyone!
Welcome 2023!

You know that moment when you realize the value you bring to all you do, that moment when you know your  brain, your heart your soul is way greater than all else. There comes that moment in most women’s lives. Some later than others and as a sex symbol I can only speak for my experience but it is the most joyous moment in life. It is that moment when you realize you are loved for so much more because you are so much more. It is a freeing moment possibly the most freeing moment as a woman the realization that your thoughts your voice your soul was always so much greater than what you attached yourself to as a crutch. Once you let that crutch go and I’m not saying be a slob be as beautiful as you want to be but know that beauty comes from within. It’s cliche but I guarantee you that moment will ultimately be the most freeing, joyous moment of your life! 🙏🏼😘

Now let’s be honest. Who doesn’t love flying first class?

You can convince yourself all you want that coach is OK but you know the only reason you’re not flying first class is because of the price tag.

Well what if I told you that there’s a secret to flying first and making it a smart money move?

What if I told you it’s a secret That many of the people you see always flying first class, like me know about?

That secret is FlyFlat. FlyFlat has saved me an average of 35% off the retail prices on long-international business and first class tickets and for the trips that have been more last minute, I’ve gotten close to 80% off before. It’s still more than coach but their discounts really do help when you’re traveling as much as me.

And the best part is they have a 24/7 concierge team that handles all your travel needs no matter how specific or last minute.

I don’t know about you, but I would much rather put that money towards a new bag or pair of loubis. So fly first, fly flat and save money with flyflat.

Malibu Beach Inn outdoes themselves every year with their views and their Thanksgiving dinner and service. One of our favorites when you want to leave the Turkey making to the experts. 
You see, Malibu is a lifestyle. And Malibu Beach Inn is the most direct beach and ocean access property in the area.  The ideal location for a luxurious and adventurous family retreat. They are ready to assist you in customizing the experience based on your family’s likes and desires.  After a day of exploring, you can enjoy cozy family time by the fireplace in your ocean front room or suite with milk & cookies, or something bubbly. This year we are grateful for the amazing sun setting as we admired it seaside. The Prime rib and Turkey were beyond as was the caramelized pumpkin pie 😍 if ever in the area I guarantee there is no better place to remind you of God’s endless bounty, where the sunset ocean views will make feeling GRATEFUL a daily occurrence.
